external_knowledge:
- Operational generators are those with a status of 1; 
- The last maintenance date is the most recent date in the maintenance records for each bus; 
- The average operating hours since the last maintenance are the average operating hours of the generators since their last maintenance; 
- A generator is considered to have at least one maintenance record if it has a non-null value for the days since the last maintenance.

sql:
SELECT status_description
FROM generator_status
WHERE status_id = 1;

SELECT bus, AVG(operating_hours) AS avg_operating_hours
FROM generators
GROUP BY bus;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_generators_count
FROM generators
WHERE Pg > 0;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM generators 
WHERE status = 1;
